'''Regio''' (pl. ''regiones'') is the [[Latin]] word for 'region.' It is used in [[planetary geology]] to refer to large areas of a [[planet]] or [[natural satellite|moon]] that are strongly differentiated in [[colour]] or [[albedo]].

